WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.680
Alif Lam Meem, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum,

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:18.200
Nazala alayka Al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrat Wa Al-Injeel,

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:22.280
Min Qabnu Hudan Li Al-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Furqan,

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:27.560
Inna Allatheena Kafuroo Bi Ayat Allahi Lahum Azaabuhu Shadeed,

00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:31.440
Wa Allahu Azizun Zuntiqan,

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:36.540
Inna Allaha La Yakhda Alayhi Shajee Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fi Al-Sama

00:00:36.540 --> 00:00:39.340
Assalamu Alaykum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuh

00:00:40.380 --> 00:00:44.560
Bismillahir Rahmanir Raheem, Alhamdulillahi Wahdahu Wa Sallallahu wa Sallam,

00:00:44.560 --> 00:00:50.380
Wa Baraka Ala Malla Nabiyya Ba'dahu Wa Ala Aalihi Wa Ashaabihi Ajma'een

00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:56.820
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, we send blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:00:57.120 --> 00:01:02.480
And all his household, his companions, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them and grant them all goodness

00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:06.600
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless every single one of us.

00:01:06.600 --> 00:01:09.040
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam,

00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:15.080
we thank Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala for giving us such a blessed month whereby we come every single night

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:19.800
for the entire month and we listen to the words of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:25.840
And above that we take home a message that we can ponder over and we can study,

00:01:25.860 --> 00:01:29.900
we can implement in our own lives and convey it to others.

00:01:29.900 --> 00:01:37.060
So thank Allah for giving us season after season, for rejuvenating and refreshing our spirituality

00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:38.860
and for granting us closeness to him.

00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:46.140
May he still grant us even more closeness to him as the days pass in such a way that the day we leave this world,

00:01:46.140 --> 00:01:49.180
we will be the closest we ever were to our own maker.

00:01:49.180 --> 00:01:52.380
May he forgive us on that day and may he grant us ease.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.340
Beloved brothers and sisters,

00:01:54.360 --> 00:02:01.200
we were looking at how the kuffar of Quraysh, the disbelievers in Quraysh had boycotted the Muslims

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:03.200
and I had made mention of several points.

00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:10.440
They said we will not marry into them nor will we allow them to marry into us.

00:02:10.440 --> 00:02:14.880
We will not deal with them nor will we allow them to deal with us.

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:20.120
We will not provide them any sustenance, anything at all that is of goodness for them.

00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:25.300
We are not going to sign a treaty with them nor will we allow them to initiate that.

00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:29.900
And we are not going to mix with them nor will we allow them to mix with us.

00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:33.420
We will not even sit with them and we will not even talk to them

00:02:33.420 --> 00:02:36.620
and we won't even allow them to enter our houses.

00:02:36.620 --> 00:02:41.180
These were some of the points that were written down.

00:02:41.180 --> 00:02:44.980
And the scribe for your information, the man who was writing it down,

00:02:44.980 --> 00:02:47.420
his name was Mansoor ibn Ikrimah.

00:02:47.420 --> 00:02:53.620
According to some of the narrations, later on he actually became paralysed on his hand.

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:55.260
He couldn't write after that.

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:57.260
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:02.660
Remember one thing, when a person harms the friends of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:05.060
wallahi there is very little hope for them

00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:11.540
because it is Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala who will retaliate instead of that particular person.

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:15.420
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us and grant us goodness.

00:03:15.420 --> 00:03:22.060
So they had written this and they had managed to get the Muslims into a place known as Shi'ab Abi Talib

00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:24.140
on the outskirts of Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:03:24.140 --> 00:03:26.940
And for three years the Muslims suffered.

00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:33.500
As we made mention of last night, they began to eat the leaves of the trees

00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:38.100
and they were sucking on the roots of some of the shrubs

00:03:38.100 --> 00:03:41.220
in order to extract the water from there.

00:03:41.220 --> 00:03:42.700
The liquid from it.

00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:51.460
And they were roasting the skins, meaning the hide of the animals that they had already cut

00:03:51.460 --> 00:03:55.540
and trying to nibble on it in order to get whatever goodness was there.

00:03:55.540 --> 00:04:01.340
They became frail, they became sick, they became very very weak and so on.

00:04:01.340 --> 00:04:04.420
It did not deter them, not at all, not at all.

00:04:04.420 --> 00:04:09.900
With us, imagine for three years if we had to be boycotted completely, no food, no drink.

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:12.380
I think three days later we probably would give in,

00:04:12.380 --> 00:04:14.820
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:18.580
The reason I make mention of this is because we are spoilt.

00:04:18.580 --> 00:04:21.100
And still we don't understand the gift of Allah.

00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:26.620
We have three meals a day and a lot of the times we have much more than we can actually eat.

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:28.380
Take a look at the month of Ramadan.

00:04:28.380 --> 00:04:33.060
Today on our tables in the evening when we were opening the fast,

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:35.580
didn't we have much more than we could consume?

00:04:35.580 --> 00:04:36.740
Allahu Akbar.

00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:39.260
That's a gift of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:04:39.260 --> 00:04:42.420
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us conscious of His gifts.

00:04:42.420 --> 00:04:45.020
What had happened then, because it was becoming very difficult,

00:04:45.020 --> 00:04:48.420
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wa sallam told his companions

00:04:48.420 --> 00:04:50.380
they may go to Habasha or to Abyssinia.

00:04:50.380 --> 00:04:54.020
Once again we made mention of this in a little bit of detail yesterday

00:04:54.020 --> 00:04:59.460
and we said that there were 83 men and 18 women who left for Abyssinia at the time

00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:03.540
and Ja'far ibn Abi Talib was the Ameer of them

00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:05.700
and Quraysh did not stop there.

00:05:05.700 --> 00:05:08.660
They sent Amr ibn al-Aas with a team of people

00:05:08.660 --> 00:05:11.540
to go to Najashi, the Negus of Abyssinia.

00:05:11.540 --> 00:05:15.140
And as we heard yesterday he went and he told the Negus

00:05:15.140 --> 00:05:18.260
that there are a group of people here from the people of Mecca,

00:05:18.260 --> 00:05:23.420
from our people who have reneged from the religion of our forefathers

00:05:23.420 --> 00:05:27.060
and they are wanted back in Mecca and they are criminals and so on.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:30.500
They have come to your land to seek asylum, send them back.

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:32.460
And these people had come with gifts,

00:05:32.460 --> 00:05:35.940
gifts to give the king, you know, to give this leader of Abyssinia.

00:05:35.940 --> 00:05:39.940
And after some time this leader Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:42.860
had already told the Muslims he would be just.

00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:46.700
He's a Christian man, he will listen to you, he will not oppress you.

00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:50.220
So he had asked Ja'far ibn Abi Talib what he had to say

00:05:50.220 --> 00:05:54.100
and after making it very clear as to why they were there

00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:57.580
and as to the ignorance they were in before

00:05:57.580 --> 00:06:01.020
and how they were blessed by Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:06:01.020 --> 00:06:05.260
being sent to them with the highest level of character and conduct

00:06:05.260 --> 00:06:07.380
and the highest level of worship.

00:06:07.380 --> 00:06:10.460
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala was to be worshiped alone.

00:06:10.460 --> 00:06:13.500
No sticks, no stones, no idols, no people,

00:06:13.500 --> 00:06:15.780
nothing besides Allah, besides the Maker,

00:06:15.780 --> 00:06:18.620
besides the one that we will return to.

00:06:18.620 --> 00:06:22.380
So in Najashi then he allowed them to stay

00:06:22.380 --> 00:06:24.700
and he told the people of Mecca to leave.

00:06:24.700 --> 00:06:28.580
The Quraysh, Amr ibn al-Aas was told to leave.

00:06:28.580 --> 00:06:29.460
And guess what?

00:06:29.460 --> 00:06:33.740
He was given back all the gifts to say take all this away and carry on.

00:06:33.740 --> 00:06:36.620
Because I didn't do what you wanted me to do here,

00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:40.420
it's like you came to me with a bribe, take it back, go away.

00:06:40.420 --> 00:06:42.700
Allahu Akbar, today when people take bribes,

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:45.420
Allah save us, even if they don't do your work for you,

00:06:45.420 --> 00:06:47.940
the bribe is eaten, Allahu Akbar, it's gone.

00:06:47.940 --> 00:06:49.460
May Allah save us.

00:06:49.460 --> 00:06:51.220
Look at the honesty of the man

00:06:51.220 --> 00:06:53.460
because they did not get what they wanted,

00:06:53.460 --> 00:06:54.460
he gave everything back.

00:06:54.460 --> 00:06:56.020
He says take this and carry on.

00:06:56.020 --> 00:06:59.780
That was a just ruler, the ruler of Abyssinia, Allahu Akbar.

00:06:59.780 --> 00:07:03.900
So they slept the night and they thought of a plan.

00:07:03.900 --> 00:07:06.780
We mentioned this yesterday, I'm repeating it today.

00:07:06.780 --> 00:07:08.540
They came back and said, do you know what?

00:07:08.540 --> 00:07:11.380
Oh, Negus of Abyssinia,

00:07:11.380 --> 00:07:14.860
these people blaspheme Jesus Christ.

00:07:14.860 --> 00:07:15.620
Do you know what?

00:07:15.620 --> 00:07:18.100
They say something very bad about Jesus,

00:07:18.100 --> 00:07:19.060
may peace be upon him.

00:07:19.060 --> 00:07:23.060
So he called Ja'far ibn Abi Talib and the Muslims

00:07:23.060 --> 00:07:25.140
and said, what do you people say about Jesus?

00:07:25.140 --> 00:07:27.500
So Ja'far ibn Abi Talib said,

00:07:27.660 --> 00:07:30.660
He is the worshipper of Allah, the slave of Allah,

00:07:30.660 --> 00:07:33.260
the messenger of Allah, subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:07:33.260 --> 00:07:36.540
The rooh, his soul was blown into the Virgin Mary,

00:07:36.540 --> 00:07:38.660
born without a father, miraculously.

00:07:38.660 --> 00:07:40.620
That's what we believe and so on.

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:43.900
And he mentioned whatever he was taught about Isa,

00:07:43.900 --> 00:07:45.820
the Prophet Jesus, may peace be upon him.

00:07:45.820 --> 00:07:49.700
And subhanallah, what did Najashi do?

00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:52.300
When he heard that, he said immediately,

00:07:52.300 --> 00:07:53.980
that he was a Christian,

00:07:54.540 --> 00:07:57.300
When he heard that, he said immediately,

00:07:57.300 --> 00:08:00.220
that is exactly what we know about the Prophet Jesus,

00:08:00.220 --> 00:08:01.540
may peace be upon him.

00:08:01.540 --> 00:08:02.820
It's exactly what we know.

00:08:02.820 --> 00:08:07.100
Imagine, this was the authentic teachings of Christianity

00:08:07.100 --> 00:08:08.500
coming from Africa.

00:08:08.500 --> 00:08:10.780
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us all.

00:08:10.780 --> 00:08:12.860
So he asked Ja'far ibn Abi Talib

00:08:12.860 --> 00:08:14.380
to read some of the Quran.

00:08:14.380 --> 00:08:16.860
And as we heard yesterday,

00:08:16.860 --> 00:08:19.340
he read the verses, opening verses of the Surah,

00:08:19.340 --> 00:08:21.540
named after Mary, the Virgin Mary,

00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:22.900
may peace be upon her,

00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:25.740
the mother of Jesus Christ, may peace be upon him.

00:08:52.900 --> 00:09:06.820
The story starts of Zakariya a.s.

00:09:06.820 --> 00:09:09.700
and how he made the dua'a in old age,

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:12.580
that, oh Allah, I'm not going to lose hope in your mercy,

00:09:12.580 --> 00:09:14.660
grant me male offspring.

00:09:14.660 --> 00:09:17.580
And how then he had children

00:09:17.580 --> 00:09:21.180
and then Mary had a child as well and so on.

00:09:21.380 --> 00:09:24.780
And the entire story of Isa a.s. is mentioned,

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:27.300
but the opening verses were enough

00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:30.460
to make the tears of Najashi roll down his eyes.

00:09:30.460 --> 00:09:32.340
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:09:32.340 --> 00:09:34.100
revelation revealed to him

00:09:34.100 --> 00:09:37.100
that An-Najashi and his men were crying

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:38.460
when they heard the Quran.

00:09:38.460 --> 00:09:42.100
And the Quran says that they believed

00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:43.420
in Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:09:43.420 --> 00:09:46.340
Although the Najashi, having accepted Islam,

00:09:46.340 --> 00:09:49.340
did not inform his subjects of it

00:09:49.340 --> 00:09:50.700
and his people of it.

00:09:50.740 --> 00:09:51.980
He kept it within.

00:09:51.980 --> 00:09:55.380
Later on, in the year 9 Hijri,

00:09:55.380 --> 00:09:56.660
according to some of the narrations

00:09:56.660 --> 00:09:58.580
and some say the 8th of Hijra,

00:09:58.580 --> 00:10:01.020
Abu Hurairah radiallahu anhu reports in a hadith

00:10:01.020 --> 00:10:02.660
which is in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:05.980
that the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:08.500
said one day that I have been informed

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:11.260
that Najashi, your brother, Ashamah,

00:10:11.260 --> 00:10:12.500
that was his name was Ashamah

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:14.300
and Najashi is just the title.

00:10:14.300 --> 00:10:15.220
It's like a king.

00:10:15.220 --> 00:10:17.860
So Ashamah and Najashi of Abyssinia

00:10:17.860 --> 00:10:19.540
has passed away your brother.

00:10:19.540 --> 00:10:22.620
Let us get up and read Salatul Janazah for him.

00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:24.660
And so they got up in abstentia

00:10:24.660 --> 00:10:27.260
and they read Salatul Janazah for An-Najashi

00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:28.620
and that was evidence enough

00:10:28.620 --> 00:10:30.620
to prove that he was a Muslim.

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:33.540
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:10:33.540 --> 00:10:36.420
and may he take us away in a condition of Iman.

00:10:36.420 --> 00:10:39.580
So these people, Amr ibn al-Aas went away.

00:10:39.580 --> 00:10:41.940
For your information, just something very interesting.

00:10:41.940 --> 00:10:45.300
Amr ibn al-Aas, he came back to Abyssinia

00:10:45.300 --> 00:10:49.260
some time later in order to try his tricks.

00:10:49.260 --> 00:10:51.260
Some time later, he came back

00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:53.620
and he spoke to the Najashi once again

00:10:53.620 --> 00:10:56.260
and Najashi told him a few words

00:10:56.260 --> 00:10:58.460
and it is reported that that is when Islam

00:10:58.460 --> 00:11:01.740
entered the heart of Amr ibn al-Aas.

00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:04.540
Islam entered the heart of Amr ibn al-Aas

00:11:04.540 --> 00:11:06.740
which means within his heart,

00:11:06.740 --> 00:11:08.500
he already began to accept

00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:11.380
because he heard someone from Africa

00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:13.580
confirm that that is a Nabi.

00:11:13.580 --> 00:11:15.420
In fact, exactly what happened was

00:11:15.420 --> 00:11:19.220
he was told that the angel

00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:20.980
that came to Jesus and Moses

00:11:20.980 --> 00:11:22.700
is the same angel that has come

00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:24.380
to the man you are talking about

00:11:24.380 --> 00:11:26.300
which is Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:11:26.300 --> 00:11:28.620
And this was witnessed by a man

00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:30.820
who lived very very far away

00:11:30.820 --> 00:11:37.620
who did not even see the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:11:37.620 --> 00:11:40.020
Now, some make mention of the fact

00:11:40.020 --> 00:11:41.900
that later on he went to Medina Munawwara

00:11:41.900 --> 00:11:44.940
and accepted in the hands of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:11:44.940 --> 00:11:46.420
that was Amr ibn al-Aas.

00:11:46.420 --> 00:11:48.900
But those who have made mention of the fact

00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:52.540
that he accepted Islam with a Najashi,

00:11:52.540 --> 00:11:53.740
there is something interesting.

00:11:53.740 --> 00:11:55.620
If that was the case,

00:11:55.620 --> 00:11:57.420
then it's the first time

00:11:57.420 --> 00:12:00.260
that a Sahabi accepted Islam

00:12:00.260 --> 00:12:02.220
at the hands of a Tabi'i.

00:12:02.220 --> 00:12:03.020
Have we thought of that?

00:12:03.020 --> 00:12:05.300
Because Najashi was a Tabi'i.

00:12:05.300 --> 00:12:08.220
He did not see Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:12:08.220 --> 00:12:10.380
So if the narration is valid,

00:12:10.380 --> 00:12:11.980
then this would have been the case.

00:12:11.980 --> 00:12:14.340
However, the more common narration is that

00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:15.980
he came back and later on

00:12:15.980 --> 00:12:17.620
he spoke to Khalid ibn al-Walid

00:12:17.620 --> 00:12:19.220
and just before the victory of Makkah,

00:12:19.220 --> 00:12:21.500
they had come in to Medina Munawwara

00:12:21.500 --> 00:12:24.700
and accepted Islam with Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:12:24.700 --> 00:12:27.660
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:12:27.660 --> 00:12:29.780
So at that particular time,

00:12:29.780 --> 00:12:33.220
whilst the Muslims were being surrounded

00:12:33.220 --> 00:12:35.100
and they were boycotted and so on,

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:37.020
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:12:37.020 --> 00:12:39.940
was suffering so much, so much suffering.

00:12:39.940 --> 00:12:40.780
Why?

00:12:40.780 --> 00:12:44.860
Because no one speaking, no one dealing,

00:12:44.860 --> 00:12:46.660
nothing happening.

00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:48.540
He decided, Allah has given me permission

00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:50.460
to go to Abyssinia, let me go.

00:12:50.460 --> 00:12:54.740
So on his way out, as he is progressing,

00:12:54.740 --> 00:12:57.900
going to Abyssinia, he meets a man who knew him.

00:12:57.900 --> 00:12:59.740
His name was Ibn al-Dughunnah.

00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:01.860
This Ibn al-Dughunnah stops him.

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:03.260
Ya Aba Bakr, where are you going?

00:13:03.260 --> 00:13:05.380
He says, I am now leaving my people.

00:13:05.380 --> 00:13:06.500
They are troubling us.

00:13:06.500 --> 00:13:08.460
They are not allowing us to follow

00:13:08.460 --> 00:13:10.180
and fulfill what we believe.

00:13:10.180 --> 00:13:11.820
So now I am going to Habashah.

00:13:11.820 --> 00:13:14.700
Perhaps Allah will open our doors there and so on.

00:13:14.700 --> 00:13:17.540
He says, no, a man like you should not be going.

00:13:17.540 --> 00:13:19.500
You are an honorable man.

00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:21.620
You fulfill the rights of everyone.

00:13:21.620 --> 00:13:24.260
Your character and conduct is exemplary.

00:13:24.260 --> 00:13:26.220
You help the widows and the orphans

00:13:26.220 --> 00:13:27.900
and you assist those in need.

00:13:27.900 --> 00:13:29.580
You do not lie and so on.

00:13:29.580 --> 00:13:31.980
Come with me, I will take you back to Quraysh

00:13:31.980 --> 00:13:33.500
and give them my guarantee

00:13:33.500 --> 00:13:35.860
that they will not harm you

00:13:35.860 --> 00:13:38.300
and they should not harm you from my guarantee.

00:13:38.300 --> 00:13:42.180
So he went back with Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:44.260
and he spoke to the leaders of Quraysh

00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:45.780
who agreed on one condition.

00:13:45.780 --> 00:13:49.580
They said, this man must not worship Allah openly

00:13:49.580 --> 00:13:51.620
and he must not recite the Qur'an openly

00:13:51.620 --> 00:13:53.300
because we've got rid of all of them.

00:13:53.300 --> 00:13:56.340
They are all somewhere in Shi'ab Abi Talib

00:13:56.340 --> 00:13:57.980
and this man here is going to come

00:13:57.980 --> 00:13:59.780
and he's going to read the Qur'an aloud.

00:13:59.780 --> 00:14:02.420
Our daughters, our sons, our children,

00:14:02.420 --> 00:14:03.700
everyone is interested.

00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:06.180
They are already turning towards these words

00:14:06.180 --> 00:14:08.620
and we don't want these words to be uttered again.

00:14:08.620 --> 00:14:10.380
We've just managed to solve the problem.

00:14:10.380 --> 00:14:11.220
For your information,

00:14:11.220 --> 00:14:13.620
if you look at the list of names of Muslims,

00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:15.460
all these top chiefs,

00:14:15.460 --> 00:14:16.740
their children were involved.

00:14:16.740 --> 00:14:18.060
They were already Muslim.

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:20.220
All the big boys, Allahu Akbar,

00:14:20.220 --> 00:14:22.180
their children were already Muslim

00:14:22.180 --> 00:14:24.180
and members of their family,

00:14:24.180 --> 00:14:26.580
either brothers, sisters, somehow relatives,

00:14:26.580 --> 00:14:27.780
very close relatives,

00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:30.660
were all already within the fold of Islam.

00:14:30.660 --> 00:14:34.860
So they knew that something drastic has to happen

00:14:34.860 --> 00:14:36.940
to block it, otherwise we are dead.

00:14:36.940 --> 00:14:37.820
What was the problem?

00:14:37.820 --> 00:14:39.100
Why were they so worried?

00:14:39.100 --> 00:14:41.940
They were worried because they feared loss of power.

00:14:41.940 --> 00:14:43.420
They feared loss of wealth.

00:14:43.420 --> 00:14:46.500
They thought some authority is going to come above us

00:14:46.500 --> 00:14:49.140
and going to take us over

00:14:49.140 --> 00:14:50.900
and then we will lose all our dignity.

00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:53.580
They did not know Islam gives dignity.

00:14:53.580 --> 00:14:55.140
It does not take it away.

00:14:55.140 --> 00:14:56.820
Allahu Akbar.

00:14:56.820 --> 00:14:59.860
So Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiAllahu anhu was free

00:14:59.860 --> 00:15:02.860
and later on, in the house,

00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:04.660
he used to read Salah outside

00:15:04.660 --> 00:15:06.420
in the little courtyard of his

00:15:06.420 --> 00:15:08.540
and people started flocking again.

00:15:08.540 --> 00:15:11.260
These people called Ibn Dughunnah after some time

00:15:11.300 --> 00:15:13.860
and told him, look, this man is breaking the promise.

00:15:13.860 --> 00:15:16.180
So Ibn Dughunnah came to him and told him,

00:15:16.180 --> 00:15:18.180
look, I gave you my guarantee

00:15:18.180 --> 00:15:19.660
and I gave the same guarantee

00:15:19.660 --> 00:15:21.500
to the people of Quraysh about you

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.060
and now you are breaking the promise

00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:24.540
by reading the Qur'an outside.

00:15:24.540 --> 00:15:26.300
Everybody is coming to listen to it

00:15:26.300 --> 00:15:28.620
and people are coming, they don't want that.

00:15:28.620 --> 00:15:32.700
So either you stop it or I take back my guarantee.

00:15:32.700 --> 00:15:34.740
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiAllahu anhu,

00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:37.060
what do you think he said?

00:15:37.060 --> 00:15:38.460
He said, take back your guarantee.

00:15:38.460 --> 00:15:39.860
Go back to him and tell them this,

00:15:39.860 --> 00:15:41.220
I can't manage.

00:15:41.220 --> 00:15:43.460
So he went back, he took the guarantee.

00:15:43.460 --> 00:15:47.140
That is when they started harming Abu Bakr radiAllahu anhu

00:15:47.140 --> 00:15:48.580
even physically.

00:15:48.580 --> 00:15:51.340
The people of Quraysh began to usurp wealth

00:15:51.340 --> 00:15:53.260
because they had got the Muslims

00:15:53.260 --> 00:15:54.900
into Shi'ab Abi Talib.

00:15:54.900 --> 00:15:56.660
So now their wealth was open.

00:15:56.660 --> 00:15:58.220
They began to usurp things

00:15:58.220 --> 00:16:00.180
and oppress in a huge way.

00:16:00.180 --> 00:16:03.260
Until one day there was a group of people

00:16:03.260 --> 00:16:06.500
who saw, in fact one man

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:09.100
and his name was Hisham ibn Amar.

00:16:09.100 --> 00:16:11.460
He was from Quraysh, not a believer.

00:16:11.460 --> 00:16:13.700
And he saw his relatives suffering

00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:16.220
because Banu al-Muttalib and Banu Hashim

00:16:16.220 --> 00:16:19.180
were in Shi'ab Abi Talib being surrounded,

00:16:19.180 --> 00:16:22.740
boycotted, suffering, dying and so on.

00:16:22.740 --> 00:16:25.100
And he says, this Hisham ibn Amar,

00:16:25.100 --> 00:16:27.580
he says to himself, we can't allow this to happen.

00:16:27.580 --> 00:16:28.820
Let me think of a plan.

00:16:28.820 --> 00:16:30.340
These are our brothers and sisters,

00:16:30.340 --> 00:16:32.540
our blood, our real family.

00:16:32.540 --> 00:16:33.700
How can this happen?

00:16:33.700 --> 00:16:34.980
He thought to himself,

00:16:34.980 --> 00:16:37.300
Abu Jahl who is the one who came up

00:16:37.340 --> 00:16:39.020
with the idea of boycott,

00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:41.540
had we come up with the idea of boycott

00:16:41.540 --> 00:16:43.940
about his family, he wouldn't have followed us.

00:16:43.940 --> 00:16:45.380
So why must we follow him?

00:16:45.380 --> 00:16:47.300
Look at this man, not a Muslim.

00:16:47.300 --> 00:16:49.820
This is why Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam says,

00:16:49.820 --> 00:16:53.820
Innallaha layu ayyidu hathad dini bil rajulil fajir.

00:16:53.820 --> 00:16:57.460
That at times Allah grants or gives support

00:16:57.460 --> 00:17:00.540
and strength to the deen by a man who is sinful,

00:17:00.540 --> 00:17:03.100
sometimes by a man who's not even a Muslim.

00:17:03.100 --> 00:17:05.020
The example of Abu Talib is cited,

00:17:05.020 --> 00:17:07.180
the example of this young man,

00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:11.220
he went to one of his friends, Zuhair ibn Abi Umayyah,

00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:13.300
and he says exactly what he thought,

00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:15.980
that look, look at these people, they are dying.

00:17:15.980 --> 00:17:17.460
We need to break this treaty.

00:17:17.460 --> 00:17:19.940
I'm ready to break it, this little covenant.

00:17:19.940 --> 00:17:21.900
I feel like going to the Kaaba and tearing it,

00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:23.620
ripping it to pieces in front of everyone,

00:17:23.620 --> 00:17:25.780
but I need one man to support me.

00:17:25.780 --> 00:17:27.980
So this man says, I'm with you.

00:17:27.980 --> 00:17:30.180
So now he went to a third man

00:17:30.180 --> 00:17:33.460
and the third man was Al-Mut'im ibn Adi.

00:17:33.460 --> 00:17:35.620
And he told Al-Mut'im ibn Adi the same thing,

00:17:35.620 --> 00:17:37.340
I need a man's support to do this.

00:17:37.340 --> 00:17:38.940
I want to tear it, rip it apart.

00:17:38.940 --> 00:17:40.460
Aren't you feeling compassionate

00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:43.780
against, meaning towards these people here?

00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:46.180
Don't you feel in your heart a little bit of mercy?

00:17:46.180 --> 00:17:47.660
He says, yes.

00:17:47.660 --> 00:17:49.780
So he says, okay, that makes now three of us.

00:17:49.780 --> 00:17:50.780
Allahu Akbar.

00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:53.340
And he went to another one, a fourth one.

00:17:53.340 --> 00:17:55.900
The fourth one was Abu al-Bakhtari ibn Hisham.

00:17:55.900 --> 00:17:57.220
And he tells him the same thing.

00:17:57.220 --> 00:17:58.540
Abu al-Bakhtari says, I'm with you.

00:17:58.540 --> 00:18:01.060
He says, now that makes four of us, Allahu Akbar.

00:18:01.060 --> 00:18:02.100
And he went to a fifth one.

00:18:02.100 --> 00:18:04.300
Look at this man and his tactic of thinking.

00:18:04.340 --> 00:18:06.940
If he were to announce it, it wouldn't have succeeded.

00:18:06.940 --> 00:18:09.620
But one by one, he went to those whom he trusts

00:18:09.620 --> 00:18:12.740
and he spoke to them on humanitarian grounds.

00:18:12.740 --> 00:18:14.700
Subhanallah, humanitarian grounds.

00:18:14.700 --> 00:18:16.260
He says, look, we need to break this.

00:18:16.260 --> 00:18:17.260
This is barbaric.

00:18:17.260 --> 00:18:20.380
How can you prevent people from eating?

00:18:20.380 --> 00:18:22.460
How can you prevent people from food and drink

00:18:22.460 --> 00:18:23.540
and they are your blood?

00:18:23.540 --> 00:18:24.700
How?

00:18:24.700 --> 00:18:27.740
So now they went to the final man, Zam'ah ibn al-Aswad

00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:29.260
and the five of them agreed.

00:18:29.260 --> 00:18:31.540
So Zuhair ibn Abi Umayyah says,

00:18:31.540 --> 00:18:33.060
let's go to the Ka'bah

00:18:33.060 --> 00:18:34.860
and we pretend like we are not connected

00:18:34.860 --> 00:18:37.660
and I will stand up in front of Abu Jahl and the others

00:18:37.660 --> 00:18:40.860
and I am going to announce that this is oppression

00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:43.100
against Banu Hashim and Banu al-Muttalib

00:18:43.100 --> 00:18:47.100
and I am going to get up and tear and rip this covenant

00:18:47.100 --> 00:18:48.380
which is on the Ka'bah

00:18:48.380 --> 00:18:50.500
and from today on, it's going to be broken.

00:18:50.500 --> 00:18:52.500
And when I say that, let's see what happens.

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:54.820
You all come in one by one to support.

00:18:55.940 --> 00:18:58.100
So this was happening on one front.

00:18:58.100 --> 00:18:59.940
On the other front,

00:18:59.940 --> 00:19:02.780
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala revealed to Muhammad

00:19:02.780 --> 00:19:04.100
salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:19:04.100 --> 00:19:07.940
O Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:09.020
three years has gone by.

00:19:09.020 --> 00:19:11.420
We want to let you know that the ants,

00:19:11.420 --> 00:19:14.140
the termites have eaten the covenant.

00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:15.140
Nothing is left of it.

00:19:15.140 --> 00:19:16.180
Besides where?

00:19:16.180 --> 00:19:18.340
The name of Allah was written.

00:19:18.340 --> 00:19:19.180
So it's eaten up.

00:19:19.180 --> 00:19:20.740
In the Ka'bah, it's in the Ka'bah

00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:22.780
but it's eaten up the termite.

00:19:22.780 --> 00:19:25.980
The mite has eaten it.

00:19:25.980 --> 00:19:27.180
So he tells his uncle,

00:19:27.180 --> 00:19:29.020
oh my uncle, this is what has happened.

00:19:29.020 --> 00:19:30.220
The uncle says, are you sure?

00:19:30.220 --> 00:19:32.500
He says, Allah has told me.

00:19:32.500 --> 00:19:33.340
Allah has told me,

00:19:33.340 --> 00:19:35.100
that's a guarantee, it's not wrong.

00:19:35.100 --> 00:19:38.260
So Abu Talib is now in the vicinity of the Ka'bah

00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.060
preparing to tell these people.

00:19:40.060 --> 00:19:41.780
And in the meantime, this man gets up.

00:19:41.780 --> 00:19:43.220
Now, these are two narrations,

00:19:43.220 --> 00:19:44.580
we brought them together.

00:19:45.540 --> 00:19:47.380
So this man, Zuhair ibn Abi Umayyah,

00:19:47.380 --> 00:19:49.580
he gets up and he makes his announcement.

00:19:49.580 --> 00:19:51.020
We want to break the covenant.

00:19:51.020 --> 00:19:52.260
I'm going to do this and do that.

00:19:52.260 --> 00:19:53.740
And Abu Jahl gets up and says,

00:19:53.740 --> 00:19:55.100
you dare touch it.

00:19:55.100 --> 00:19:57.220
So now Hisham ibn Amr gets up and says,

00:19:57.220 --> 00:19:58.180
what are you talking about?

00:19:58.180 --> 00:19:59.820
I agree with this man here.

00:19:59.820 --> 00:20:02.180
It is wrong, it is oppressive and so on.

00:20:02.180 --> 00:20:03.820
So Abu Jahl says, who you think you are?

00:20:03.820 --> 00:20:05.100
And the third one gets up and says,

00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:07.100
no, I also agree with these two.

00:20:07.100 --> 00:20:08.340
What they are saying is right.

00:20:08.340 --> 00:20:09.700
And then a few people get in

00:20:09.700 --> 00:20:12.180
and the fourth one comes and the fifth one comes.

00:20:12.180 --> 00:20:14.820
And then Abu Talib says, hang on.

00:20:14.820 --> 00:20:17.900
This covenant has been eaten by ants.

00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:20.740
And this was information given to my nephew

00:20:20.740 --> 00:20:22.340
by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:25.300
Everyone is silent.

00:20:25.300 --> 00:20:26.740
They are silent.

00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:27.980
What is the silence?

00:20:27.980 --> 00:20:29.340
The covenant is eaten.

00:20:29.340 --> 00:20:31.540
So Quraish get together quickly

00:20:31.540 --> 00:20:34.020
and they tell Abu Talib, okay,

00:20:34.020 --> 00:20:35.580
what if the covenant is not eaten?

00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:37.500
He says, if the covenant is not eaten,

00:20:37.500 --> 00:20:38.940
I hand you my nephew.

00:20:38.940 --> 00:20:39.740
I give him to you.

00:20:39.740 --> 00:20:40.740
That's all they wanted.

00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:43.100
They wanted him to execute him.

00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:44.260
I hand him to him.

00:20:44.260 --> 00:20:46.340
And if the covenant is eaten,

00:20:46.340 --> 00:20:48.420
the boycott stops immediately.

00:20:48.420 --> 00:20:51.660
They agreed and they struck that agreement properly.

00:20:51.660 --> 00:20:53.660
And then they look into the Kaaba.

00:20:53.660 --> 00:20:55.380
They see, low and behold,

00:20:55.380 --> 00:20:58.700
it is completely eaten besides the name of Allah.

00:20:58.700 --> 00:21:00.340
Subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:21:00.340 --> 00:21:02.380
And these young boys were successful.

00:21:02.380 --> 00:21:03.540
And at the same time,

00:21:03.540 --> 00:21:05.180
the revelation that had come to Muhammad

00:21:05.180 --> 00:21:07.460
salallahu alayhi wa sallam as well

00:21:07.460 --> 00:21:10.140
was completely accurate, subhanallah.

00:21:10.140 --> 00:21:12.860
Still, the boycott, mashallah,

00:21:12.860 --> 00:21:14.100
it had stopped immediately,

00:21:14.100 --> 00:21:15.900
but they didn't believe.

00:21:15.900 --> 00:21:19.100
And what is of irony is Abu Talib himself

00:21:19.100 --> 00:21:20.740
also did not believe yet.

00:21:20.740 --> 00:21:21.900
That's very ironic.

00:21:21.900 --> 00:21:23.500
And this goes to show that sometimes

00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:26.540
when Allah has not written guidance for someone,

00:21:26.540 --> 00:21:27.500
it will never come.

00:21:27.540 --> 00:21:29.540
It's our teaching.

00:21:29.540 --> 00:21:31.780
We are taught by Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:21:31.780 --> 00:21:33.140
to constantly say,

00:21:33.140 --> 00:21:35.540
اللهم يا مقلب القلوب

00:21:35.540 --> 00:21:37.300
ثبت قلوبنا على دينك

00:21:37.300 --> 00:21:39.100
O Allah, O Allah,

00:21:39.100 --> 00:21:40.740
who turns the hearts,

00:21:40.740 --> 00:21:43.500
the one who owns the turning of the hearts,

00:21:43.500 --> 00:21:46.180
turn our hearts upon the right path,

00:21:46.180 --> 00:21:48.140
not away from it.

00:21:48.140 --> 00:21:49.780
Because Allah owns the hearts.

00:21:49.780 --> 00:21:50.300
We say,

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:52.380
اهدنا الصراط المستقيم

00:21:52.380 --> 00:21:54.340
Guide us to the straight path.

00:21:54.340 --> 00:21:57.180
Because guidance is in the hands of Allah.

00:21:57.180 --> 00:21:59.180
Subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:21:59.180 --> 00:22:00.780
if Allah seals the hearts,

00:22:00.780 --> 00:22:04.100
who is going to guide those hearts thereafter?

00:22:04.100 --> 00:22:05.540
So may Allah open our doors.

00:22:05.540 --> 00:22:06.940
Some people see the light.

00:22:06.940 --> 00:22:08.700
They see it bright shining,

00:22:08.700 --> 00:22:10.380
but they don't want to take heed

00:22:10.380 --> 00:22:12.260
and they don't want to learn lesson.

00:22:12.260 --> 00:22:16.500
So this was revelation from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:16.500 --> 00:22:18.460
and these boys, subhanallah,

00:22:18.460 --> 00:22:19.900
these youngsters of Quraysh,

00:22:19.900 --> 00:22:21.340
they had succeeded.

00:22:21.340 --> 00:22:24.540
And the boycott was over.

00:22:24.540 --> 00:22:26.380
And now the people of Quraysh

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:29.260
began to persecute the Muslims once again.

00:22:29.260 --> 00:22:31.540
A very, very great degree.

00:22:31.540 --> 00:22:33.900
And what had happened at that particular point,

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:36.180
Allah blessed Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:22:36.180 --> 00:22:37.460
with a blessing.

00:22:37.460 --> 00:22:39.060
The people of Najran,

00:22:39.060 --> 00:22:41.740
Najran was a distance from Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:22:41.740 --> 00:22:44.300
They were predominantly Christian people.

00:22:44.300 --> 00:22:46.300
They had heard about this messenger

00:22:46.300 --> 00:22:49.260
and they decided to send a group of people,

00:22:49.260 --> 00:22:50.580
mashallah,

00:22:50.580 --> 00:22:52.980
to go and see this man

00:22:52.980 --> 00:22:54.220
and to get news

00:22:54.220 --> 00:22:55.860
and to see whether he is right or wrong.

00:22:55.860 --> 00:22:58.420
So the Christians of Najran

00:22:58.420 --> 00:23:02.540
sent 20 men to Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:23:02.540 --> 00:23:06.220
when they had come out of the boycott.

00:23:06.220 --> 00:23:09.140
And they came and asked him questions.

00:23:09.140 --> 00:23:10.620
And they asked him,

00:23:10.620 --> 00:23:12.060
they heard some of the Qur'an

00:23:12.060 --> 00:23:13.380
asking him questions.

00:23:13.380 --> 00:23:16.020
All 20 accepted Islam one go.

00:23:16.020 --> 00:23:16.860
Allahu akbar.

00:23:16.860 --> 00:23:17.700
They all accepted.

00:23:17.700 --> 00:23:20.180
Look, the people of Quraysh did not accept,

00:23:20.180 --> 00:23:23.580
but people from far away came and accepted.

00:23:23.580 --> 00:23:24.660
This is what happens

00:23:24.660 --> 00:23:26.540
to the Anbiya of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:23:26.540 --> 00:23:27.580
Their own people,

00:23:27.580 --> 00:23:28.500
boot them out.

00:23:28.500 --> 00:23:30.380
This is what Waraka bin Naufal said.

00:23:30.380 --> 00:23:32.900
When you come with this message to your people,

00:23:32.900 --> 00:23:34.100
they're not going to listen to you.

00:23:34.100 --> 00:23:36.460
But the others further away

00:23:36.460 --> 00:23:38.780
will benefit from it much, much more

00:23:38.780 --> 00:23:39.860
than your own people.

00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:42.180
May Allah grant us really a lesson.

00:23:42.180 --> 00:23:43.780
I always like to make mention

00:23:43.780 --> 00:23:45.860
of the ulama of your area.

00:23:45.860 --> 00:23:47.900
Every time there are ulama in your midst,

00:23:47.900 --> 00:23:48.860
make use of them.

00:23:48.860 --> 00:23:50.260
If you don't make use of them,

00:23:50.260 --> 00:23:51.860
there will be others further away

00:23:51.860 --> 00:23:53.340
who will be making use of them

00:23:53.340 --> 00:23:56.620
and you will go without any form of goodness,

00:23:56.620 --> 00:23:57.900
without having benefited.

00:23:57.900 --> 00:23:59.940
When you meet Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:23:59.940 --> 00:24:00.980
He will ask you,

00:24:00.980 --> 00:24:03.060
I kept so and so and so and so

00:24:03.060 --> 00:24:05.060
right near you as your neighbors.

00:24:05.060 --> 00:24:07.380
How did you not benefit from them?

00:24:07.380 --> 00:24:08.580
They had the message.

00:24:08.580 --> 00:24:10.060
You didn't even get the message.

00:24:10.060 --> 00:24:12.820
So ensure that you make use

00:24:12.820 --> 00:24:14.220
of the ulama in your midst.

00:24:14.220 --> 00:24:16.900
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala help us.

00:24:16.900 --> 00:24:18.500
May Allah open our doors.

00:24:18.500 --> 00:24:20.620
The lesson we have just learned is from

00:24:20.620 --> 00:24:21.460
what happened?

00:24:21.460 --> 00:24:22.940
The people of Najran came.

00:24:22.940 --> 00:24:24.420
What about the people of Makkah?

00:24:24.420 --> 00:24:25.820
His own family rejected.

00:24:25.820 --> 00:24:26.620
Allahu Akbar.

00:24:26.620 --> 00:24:28.620
His own uncle and the others.

00:24:28.620 --> 00:24:31.020
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not prohibit us.

00:24:31.020 --> 00:24:33.340
So Abu Jahl looks at these people of Najran

00:24:33.340 --> 00:24:35.100
and he says, you people are mad.

00:24:35.100 --> 00:24:36.820
How can you have come here,

00:24:36.820 --> 00:24:38.860
ask one, two questions and you accept

00:24:38.860 --> 00:24:40.980
when we live here and we know this man

00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:42.500
and we will never accept.

00:24:42.500 --> 00:24:45.340
So immediately Allahu Akbar,

00:24:45.340 --> 00:24:47.020
they responded.

00:24:47.020 --> 00:24:48.660
They said, look, we have our choice.

00:24:48.660 --> 00:24:49.580
We have chosen.

00:24:49.580 --> 00:24:50.420
You have your choice.

00:24:50.420 --> 00:24:51.260
You've chosen.

00:24:51.260 --> 00:24:52.100
And you know what?

00:24:52.100 --> 00:24:55.460
You don't want to debate with someone who's a fool.

00:24:55.460 --> 00:24:57.180
And Allah revealed verses to Muhammad

00:24:57.180 --> 00:24:58.820
salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:24:58.820 --> 00:25:09.860
وَإِذَا سَمِعٌ لَغْوَ أَعْرَضُوا عَنُّ وَقَالُوا لَنَا أَعْمَالُنَا وَلَكُمْ أَعْمَالُكُمْ سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكُمْ

00:25:09.860 --> 00:25:14.300
لَا نَبْتَغِ الْجَاهِلِينَ

00:25:14.300 --> 00:25:16.140
When they hear the foolish person,

00:25:16.140 --> 00:25:18.140
when they hear that which is vain,

00:25:18.140 --> 00:25:20.460
what Abu Jahl was saying.

00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:23.260
When they hear that which is vain,

00:25:23.260 --> 00:25:24.540
they turned away from it.

00:25:24.540 --> 00:25:25.900
They turned away from it.

00:25:25.900 --> 00:25:28.180
And they said, we have our deeds, our choice.

00:25:28.180 --> 00:25:29.900
You have your deeds, your choice.

00:25:29.900 --> 00:25:31.540
And peace be upon you.

00:25:31.540 --> 00:25:33.220
We are not going to waste our time

00:25:33.220 --> 00:25:34.580
debating and arguing with you.

00:25:34.580 --> 00:25:37.220
So this verse was revealed in connection

00:25:37.220 --> 00:25:40.180
with the group that had come from Najran

00:25:40.180 --> 00:25:42.900
and what debate or what little discussion

00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:44.500
they had had with Abu Jahl.

00:25:44.500 --> 00:25:47.420
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us lesson.

00:25:47.420 --> 00:25:48.700
Then Allahu Akbar,

00:25:48.700 --> 00:25:51.940
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala makes mention

00:25:51.940 --> 00:25:54.420
of something very, very powerful,

00:25:54.420 --> 00:25:57.700
connected to something that had happened

00:25:57.700 --> 00:26:00.580
that was very sad on one hand

00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:03.660
and the other hand a lesson for all.

00:26:03.660 --> 00:26:06.820
The uncle of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:26:06.820 --> 00:26:09.900
fell ill, he fell sick.

00:26:09.900 --> 00:26:14.180
And Quraysh, they were happy and they were sad.

00:26:14.180 --> 00:26:15.780
They were happy and they were sad.

00:26:15.780 --> 00:26:17.220
They were sad thinking this man

00:26:17.260 --> 00:26:19.700
is going to accept Islam last minute.

00:26:19.700 --> 00:26:22.020
And they were happy because they thought to themselves,

00:26:22.020 --> 00:26:25.300
once he's gone, we can nail this man as we like.

00:26:25.300 --> 00:26:27.420
Allahu Akbar, may Allah protect us.

00:26:27.420 --> 00:26:30.500
This nephew, he was being protected by the uncle.

00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:32.900
The uncle dies, we can do whatever we want

00:26:32.900 --> 00:26:34.220
with this nephew.

00:26:34.220 --> 00:26:37.260
So they made sure they were around Abu Talib

00:26:37.260 --> 00:26:38.140
on his death bed.

00:26:38.140 --> 00:26:41.020
He was now very old and sickly.

00:26:41.020 --> 00:26:42.820
And the Prophet peace be upon him

00:26:42.820 --> 00:26:44.540
who loved his uncle a lot,

00:26:44.540 --> 00:26:46.340
meaning he had great care for his uncle.

00:26:46.380 --> 00:26:47.860
His uncle cared for him.

00:26:47.860 --> 00:26:51.020
But when Islam came, he continued trying

00:26:51.020 --> 00:26:53.420
to convey the message of Islam to his uncle.

00:26:53.420 --> 00:26:55.540
His uncle knew what was right and wrong,

00:26:55.540 --> 00:26:57.260
but he had not uttered the Shahadah.

00:26:57.260 --> 00:26:59.380
He didn't declare it.

00:26:59.380 --> 00:27:01.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:27:01.300 --> 00:27:02.980
not only the utterance of Shahadah,

00:27:02.980 --> 00:27:05.820
but the belief and the ability to convey to others.

00:27:05.820 --> 00:27:07.140
Ameen.

00:27:07.140 --> 00:27:09.860
So his uncle, the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:27:09.860 --> 00:27:10.700
looks at him and says,

00:27:10.700 --> 00:27:14.700
Ya am, qul kalimatan uhajulaka biha yawmal qiyama

00:27:14.740 --> 00:27:16.980
I want you to utter one statement

00:27:16.980 --> 00:27:19.380
so that I can fight your case on the day of qiyama.

00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:20.220
Allahu Akbar.

00:27:20.220 --> 00:27:22.780
You utter one statement and the rest is mine,

00:27:22.780 --> 00:27:23.860
so to speak.

00:27:23.860 --> 00:27:25.660
Say one word, I will bear witness

00:27:25.660 --> 00:27:27.660
on the day of qiyama that you have uttered it.

00:27:27.660 --> 00:27:29.980
Just say that there is none worthy of worship

00:27:29.980 --> 00:27:31.300
besides the maker and the one

00:27:31.300 --> 00:27:32.340
you are going to return to.

00:27:32.340 --> 00:27:33.220
Just say that.

00:27:33.220 --> 00:27:35.980
Once you utter that, I will do the rest for you.

00:27:35.980 --> 00:27:36.980
Allahu Akbar.

00:27:36.980 --> 00:27:39.220
Because you need to turn away from the idols

00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:41.300
and all what Quraish was worshiping

00:27:41.300 --> 00:27:42.500
and you need to come to the worship

00:27:42.500 --> 00:27:44.260
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:27:44.260 --> 00:27:47.180
But the uncle, he actually tells his nephew,

00:27:47.180 --> 00:27:50.420
oh, my nephew, had it not been

00:27:50.420 --> 00:27:52.220
for these big boys around me,

00:27:52.220 --> 00:27:55.340
meaning the big people of Quraish around me,

00:27:55.340 --> 00:27:58.260
I would have made you so happy by that statement.

00:27:58.260 --> 00:28:01.100
But if I now say it on my deathbed,

00:28:01.100 --> 00:28:03.140
it's going to be a great embarrassment.

00:28:03.140 --> 00:28:05.980
I will go down as a traitor in history.

00:28:05.980 --> 00:28:07.580
Look at this.

00:28:07.580 --> 00:28:09.340
This is what the man says.

00:28:09.340 --> 00:28:11.300
If it wasn't for Quraish around here,

00:28:11.300 --> 00:28:12.140
I would be uttering.

00:28:12.140 --> 00:28:13.300
And Quraish was waiting,

00:28:13.340 --> 00:28:15.340
meaning the head, they were waiting there

00:28:15.340 --> 00:28:17.740
because they knew, we don't want tomorrow

00:28:17.740 --> 00:28:20.620
to hear that on his deathbed he became a Muslim

00:28:20.620 --> 00:28:21.460
and we didn't know.

00:28:21.460 --> 00:28:22.620
So we want to bear witness,

00:28:22.620 --> 00:28:25.100
we are going to be here right here.

00:28:25.100 --> 00:28:26.740
So the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:28:26.740 --> 00:28:29.060
was very sad because he kept repeating this,

00:28:29.060 --> 00:28:31.300
that oh, my uncle, utter one statement.

00:28:31.300 --> 00:28:33.500
Just say la ilaha illallah

00:28:33.500 --> 00:28:35.100
and I will bear witness for you.

00:28:35.100 --> 00:28:39.350
Muhammadur Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:28:39.350 --> 00:28:40.910
But the uncle passed away.

00:28:40.910 --> 00:28:42.030
When the uncle passed away

00:28:42.030 --> 00:28:43.670
without having uttered these words,

00:28:43.670 --> 00:28:45.070
the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:28:45.070 --> 00:28:46.310
was very, very sad.

00:28:46.310 --> 00:28:47.510
Very, very sad.

00:28:47.510 --> 00:28:49.070
And this is when verses were revealed

00:28:49.070 --> 00:28:51.110
by Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:28:51.110 --> 00:28:55.590
Innaka la tahdi man ahbabta

00:28:55.590 --> 00:29:03.310
wa lakinna allaha yahdi main yashaa

00:29:03.310 --> 00:29:06.110
You do not guide whomever you wish.

00:29:06.110 --> 00:29:08.030
Oh, Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:29:08.030 --> 00:29:11.510
we guide, Allah guides whomever he wishes.

00:29:11.510 --> 00:29:12.830
Subhanallah.

00:29:12.830 --> 00:29:15.110
So guidance is not in your hands.

00:29:15.110 --> 00:29:16.630
Guidance is in the hands of Allah.

00:29:16.630 --> 00:29:19.150
In your hands is to show the path.

00:29:19.150 --> 00:29:21.190
Whether they walk on it or not

00:29:21.190 --> 00:29:23.310
is up to Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:29:23.310 --> 00:29:27.190
You see, Hidayah is divided into two categories.

00:29:27.190 --> 00:29:27.950
Like Allah says,

00:29:27.950 --> 00:29:30.590
wa innaka la tahdi ila siratil mustaqeem

00:29:30.590 --> 00:29:32.150
Oh, Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:29:32.150 --> 00:29:34.270
you guide them to the straight path,

00:29:34.270 --> 00:29:37.110
which means you show them where the path is.

00:29:37.110 --> 00:29:39.270
But the guidance as in the ability

00:29:39.270 --> 00:29:40.550
to walk on that path,

00:29:40.550 --> 00:29:42.790
that's only in the hands of Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:29:42.790 --> 00:29:45.350
So let's not confuse the two types of guidance.

00:29:45.350 --> 00:29:47.710
One is ad-dalala wal irshad.

00:29:47.710 --> 00:29:49.270
The other one is tawfiq,

00:29:49.270 --> 00:29:51.550
where Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala gives acceptance

00:29:51.550 --> 00:29:53.110
to a person to walk on the path.

00:29:53.110 --> 00:29:55.150
A lot of us know what is right and wrong,

00:29:55.150 --> 00:29:58.070
but a lot of us are guilty of slipping here and there

00:29:58.070 --> 00:29:59.550
and doing that which is wrong

00:29:59.550 --> 00:30:01.470
and not doing that which we are supposed to.

00:30:01.470 --> 00:30:02.390
So this happens.

00:30:02.390 --> 00:30:05.190
May Allah forgive us and make us strong.

00:30:05.190 --> 00:30:07.950
So to know what's right and wrong is one thing,

00:30:07.950 --> 00:30:10.590
but to walk on that path is another thing.

00:30:10.590 --> 00:30:12.390
So this was also a verse that was revealed

00:30:12.390 --> 00:30:14.310
to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:30:14.310 --> 00:30:16.710
Now there was a very, very difficult time

00:30:16.710 --> 00:30:19.590
that Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:30:19.590 --> 00:30:21.190
had gone through, very difficult,

00:30:21.190 --> 00:30:23.030
because his uncle passed away.

00:30:23.030 --> 00:30:24.950
The people of Quraysh began,

00:30:24.950 --> 00:30:26.110
they already threatened,

00:30:26.110 --> 00:30:27.830
now we're going to kill this man.

00:30:27.830 --> 00:30:31.150
And do you know Abu Talib was the external support,

00:30:31.150 --> 00:30:35.750
which means he protected Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:38.750
from any external harm by the will of Allah.

00:30:39.670 --> 00:30:42.030
But something else happened.

00:30:42.030 --> 00:30:44.710
Khadija binti Khuwailid radiallahu anha,

00:30:44.710 --> 00:30:47.870
who was the closest to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:30:47.870 --> 00:30:48.790
his own wife,

00:30:48.790 --> 00:30:51.190
who was the biggest pillar of support and comfort.

00:30:51.190 --> 00:30:53.430
She also fell ill and passed away.

00:30:53.430 --> 00:30:55.230
Khadija radiallahu anha,

00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:57.150
this was in the tenth year of Hijra.

00:30:57.150 --> 00:30:59.830
It became known as the year of sadness,

00:30:59.830 --> 00:31:01.470
because one after the other,

00:31:01.470 --> 00:31:03.470
negativities came into place,

00:31:03.470 --> 00:31:05.230
what we would term negativities.

00:31:05.230 --> 00:31:06.990
But Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:31:06.990 --> 00:31:08.110
although he was sad,

00:31:08.150 --> 00:31:09.230
he knew Allah's plan.

00:31:09.230 --> 00:31:10.310
He was a Nabi,

00:31:10.310 --> 00:31:11.750
and he knew there is a plan.

00:31:11.750 --> 00:31:15.150
He knew that these words and this message

00:31:15.150 --> 00:31:19.510
have to go across wherever there are human beings,

00:31:19.510 --> 00:31:21.550
wherever there are mankind or jinn kind,

00:31:21.550 --> 00:31:24.070
the message is definitely going to reach.

00:31:24.070 --> 00:31:25.550
He lost his uncle,

00:31:25.550 --> 00:31:26.750
he lost his wife.

00:31:26.750 --> 00:31:27.830
The uncle, as I said,

00:31:27.830 --> 00:31:30.230
protected him from external harm.

00:31:30.230 --> 00:31:33.030
The wife protected him internally,

00:31:33.030 --> 00:31:34.030
comforted him.

00:31:34.030 --> 00:31:36.070
So he lost that inner comfort

00:31:36.150 --> 00:31:40.630
and the outer comfort zone that he had had all along.

00:31:40.630 --> 00:31:41.950
This was a test.

00:31:41.950 --> 00:31:43.230
Now he thought to himself,

00:31:43.230 --> 00:31:44.390
Subhanallah,

00:31:44.390 --> 00:31:47.710
the people of Quraysh are planning to kill me.

00:31:47.710 --> 00:31:49.470
They want to kick me out.

00:31:49.470 --> 00:31:53.620
They want to boycott.

00:31:53.620 --> 00:31:55.020
They want to surround.

00:31:55.020 --> 00:31:56.420
They want to persecute.

00:31:56.420 --> 00:31:57.740
They want to do so many things.

00:31:57.740 --> 00:31:59.500
Allah makes mention in the Quran.

00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:02.660
وَإِذْ يَمْكُرُ بِكَ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا

00:32:02.660 --> 00:32:06.580
لِيُثْبِتُكَ أَوْ يَقُتُلُكَ أَوْ يُخْرِجُكَ

00:32:06.580 --> 00:32:09.780
وَيَمْكُرُونَ وَيَمْكُرُوا اللَّهِ

00:32:09.780 --> 00:32:11.260
These kuffar,

00:32:11.260 --> 00:32:15.020
they were planning to keep you on one spot,

00:32:15.020 --> 00:32:16.540
which means to ground you,

00:32:16.540 --> 00:32:17.100
number one,

00:32:17.100 --> 00:32:18.740
or to kill you,

00:32:18.740 --> 00:32:21.420
or to expel you.

00:32:21.420 --> 00:32:22.340
They were planning,

00:32:22.340 --> 00:32:23.060
Allah plans,

00:32:23.060 --> 00:32:25.020
and Allah is the best of planners.

00:32:25.020 --> 00:32:27.580
So Rasulullah ﷺ thought to himself,

00:32:27.620 --> 00:32:29.500
you see the people of Ta'if,

00:32:29.500 --> 00:32:31.340
they are the closest people.

00:32:31.340 --> 00:32:33.580
It's the next city,

00:32:33.580 --> 00:32:34.340
the next city,

00:32:34.340 --> 00:32:35.980
closest to Makkah al-Mukarramah,

00:32:35.980 --> 00:32:36.820
not too far.

00:32:36.820 --> 00:32:37.940
Let me go there,

00:32:37.940 --> 00:32:39.780
and perhaps I will try with them.

00:32:39.780 --> 00:32:41.340
If I win their support,

00:32:41.340 --> 00:32:43.220
perhaps we could come into Quraysh

00:32:43.220 --> 00:32:44.100
and explain to them,

00:32:44.100 --> 00:32:45.980
and perhaps they would then seeing

00:32:45.980 --> 00:32:48.460
how many people of Ta'if have accepted Islam,

00:32:48.460 --> 00:32:50.020
they would embrace Islam.

00:32:50.020 --> 00:32:52.460
So the Prophet ﷺ on one hand,

00:32:52.460 --> 00:32:54.380
some of his people are gone to Abyssinia.

00:32:54.380 --> 00:32:55.220
The other hand,

00:32:55.260 --> 00:32:57.700
people in Makkah al-Mukarramah are being persecuted.

00:32:57.700 --> 00:32:59.300
And now what is happening?

00:32:59.300 --> 00:33:01.500
He takes Zayd ibn Haritha,

00:33:01.500 --> 00:33:04.740
who was the closest person to him as well now,

00:33:04.740 --> 00:33:07.020
and he walks to Al-Ta'if.

00:33:07.020 --> 00:33:08.780
They went on foot.

00:33:08.780 --> 00:33:09.700
Why did they go on foot?

00:33:09.700 --> 00:33:11.740
Because had they gone on horseback, camelback,

00:33:11.740 --> 00:33:13.620
people would know these people are now leaving Makkah.

00:33:13.620 --> 00:33:14.780
They would get excited.

00:33:14.780 --> 00:33:15.860
They wouldn't allow them to go

00:33:15.860 --> 00:33:17.580
because they would want him back.

00:33:17.580 --> 00:33:21.540
They did not want Muhammad ﷺ to go elsewhere

00:33:21.540 --> 00:33:25.180
because as much as they didn't like him,

00:33:25.180 --> 00:33:27.220
they knew that people from outside

00:33:27.220 --> 00:33:28.940
were coming and accepting the message.

00:33:28.940 --> 00:33:29.780
They knew it.

00:33:29.780 --> 00:33:32.500
So they were confused, these people of Quraysh.

00:33:32.500 --> 00:33:34.220
One hand they're saying, we're gonna expel him.

00:33:34.220 --> 00:33:35.580
On another hand they say,

00:33:35.580 --> 00:33:37.940
no, we're gonna keep him here and ground him.

00:33:37.940 --> 00:33:39.780
We don't want anyone to talk to him.

00:33:39.780 --> 00:33:42.220
So Rasulullah ﷺ went to Ta'if.

00:33:42.220 --> 00:33:43.460
When he went to Ta'if,

00:33:43.460 --> 00:33:46.380
he immediately headed for the leaders of Ta'if.

00:33:46.380 --> 00:33:47.220
Who were they?

00:33:48.660 --> 00:33:51.540
Abdi Alil, that was one, ibn Amr

00:33:51.540 --> 00:33:53.060
and his two brothers,

00:33:53.060 --> 00:33:55.740
Masood ibn Amr and Habib ibn Amr.

00:33:55.740 --> 00:33:57.420
These were the three people.

00:33:57.420 --> 00:33:58.260
He went to them.

00:33:58.260 --> 00:33:59.100
He spoke to them.

00:33:59.100 --> 00:34:00.460
He presented Islam to them.

00:34:00.460 --> 00:34:03.500
It is reported that in total he was 10 days in Ta'if

00:34:03.500 --> 00:34:05.900
and he presented Islam to them in a beautiful way.

00:34:05.900 --> 00:34:09.300
And he told them about Allah and about the idols

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:11.180
and about good character and conduct

00:34:11.180 --> 00:34:13.100
and not burying the girls alive

00:34:13.100 --> 00:34:15.700
and not engaging in misbehavior and misconduct

00:34:15.700 --> 00:34:17.940
and cheating and deceiving and waylaying

00:34:17.940 --> 00:34:21.100
and being, robbing the traveler and so on.

00:34:21.100 --> 00:34:25.140
And he told them also of Quraysh and their persecution.

00:34:25.140 --> 00:34:26.100
Now these people,

00:34:27.860 --> 00:34:31.300
they did not accept the message, number one.

00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:32.380
Number two is,

00:34:32.380 --> 00:34:34.100
Muhammad ﷺ told them,

00:34:34.100 --> 00:34:36.180
okay, if you don't want to accept the message,

00:34:36.180 --> 00:34:38.460
no problem, but please do me one favor.

00:34:38.460 --> 00:34:40.380
Don't tell Quraysh that I was here

00:34:40.380 --> 00:34:43.700
because if they know that I am seeking protection

00:34:43.700 --> 00:34:46.740
and I'm seeking your assistance to go and fight them,

00:34:46.740 --> 00:34:49.620
then there is going to be a lot of trouble.

00:34:49.620 --> 00:34:50.540
What did they do?

00:34:50.540 --> 00:34:52.660
They sent a messenger straight to Quraysh.

00:34:52.660 --> 00:34:54.780
This man, he came to us

00:34:54.780 --> 00:34:58.460
and he is trying to win our support against you.

00:34:58.460 --> 00:35:00.980
The reason is the two of them had their squabbles.

00:35:00.980 --> 00:35:02.940
Now in order to settle it a little bit,

00:35:02.940 --> 00:35:04.580
they quickly went to tell, to say,

00:35:04.580 --> 00:35:07.060
you know what, this man here is a middle man here

00:35:07.060 --> 00:35:09.140
and we are going to deal with him.

00:35:09.140 --> 00:35:10.620
And in the meantime, these three,

00:35:10.620 --> 00:35:14.140
instead of sending him away respectfully to say,

00:35:14.140 --> 00:35:16.620
look, we don't accept your message,

00:35:16.620 --> 00:35:19.300
they sent the children and the slaves,

00:35:19.300 --> 00:35:22.020
boys and girls out on the streets

00:35:22.020 --> 00:35:26.260
and told them stone this man and mock at him

00:35:26.260 --> 00:35:28.340
and do whatever you want to him

00:35:28.340 --> 00:35:29.740
and nothing will happen to you.

00:35:29.740 --> 00:35:30.860
We are the leaders.

00:35:30.860 --> 00:35:32.340
We're going to sit here and watch.

00:35:32.340 --> 00:35:33.660
A'udhu Billah.

00:35:33.660 --> 00:35:36.260
So as Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:35:36.260 --> 00:35:39.060
had taken a message of peace and goodness

00:35:39.060 --> 00:35:40.820
to the people of Ta'if,

00:35:40.820 --> 00:35:43.980
they retaliated with stones and sticks.

00:35:43.980 --> 00:35:46.620
They threw stones, they hurled abuse.

00:35:46.620 --> 00:35:48.060
They made him bleed.

00:35:48.060 --> 00:35:53.900
He was harmed and he was hurt on his body

00:35:53.900 --> 00:35:57.020
and the blood was now trickling in his shoes.

00:35:57.020 --> 00:36:00.700
His shoes were filled and he is going out of Ta'if

00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:02.540
and they are running behind him

00:36:02.540 --> 00:36:03.980
and they are pelting him

00:36:03.980 --> 00:36:05.620
and they are laughing at him

00:36:05.620 --> 00:36:08.060
as though they were pelting a dog.

00:36:08.060 --> 00:36:09.300
A'udhu Billah.

00:36:09.300 --> 00:36:10.620
May Allah save us.

00:36:10.620 --> 00:36:12.740
And this is the best of creation

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:15.620
who came to them with a message of goodness.

00:36:15.620 --> 00:36:18.700
These were the people of Ta'if.

00:36:18.700 --> 00:36:20.380
And what had happened?

00:36:20.380 --> 00:36:24.660
Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala sent Jibreel Alaihi Salatu Wa Salam

00:36:24.660 --> 00:36:26.820
to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:36:26.820 --> 00:36:29.740
A few pointers of mercy.

00:36:29.740 --> 00:36:30.820
One is he says,

00:36:30.820 --> 00:36:33.540
O Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:36:33.540 --> 00:36:35.420
we have watched what they have done to you.

00:36:35.420 --> 00:36:37.620
We know what they have done to you.

00:36:37.620 --> 00:36:38.900
You instruct us.

00:36:38.900 --> 00:36:42.020
We will do to them what you wish.

00:36:42.020 --> 00:36:44.780
Then it is reported according to one narration

00:36:44.780 --> 00:36:46.420
although some of the scholars of Hadith

00:36:46.420 --> 00:36:47.940
say that this narration is mursal.

00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:51.220
Mursal meaning the chain is not complete near the end.

00:36:51.220 --> 00:36:54.420
So there was a man known as Addas.

00:36:54.420 --> 00:36:57.420
He was a slave of Utbah and Shaybah Ibn Rabi'ah

00:36:57.420 --> 00:36:59.540
and they had had a little garden in Ta'if,

00:36:59.540 --> 00:37:00.860
on the outskirts of Ta'if.

00:37:00.860 --> 00:37:02.540
So as Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:37:02.540 --> 00:37:03.900
was running out,

00:37:03.900 --> 00:37:05.220
he found a little shrubbery

00:37:05.220 --> 00:37:08.220
where the grapes were growing.

00:37:08.220 --> 00:37:10.980
So he ducked underneath it.

00:37:10.980 --> 00:37:12.820
Him and Zaid Ibn Haritha.

00:37:12.860 --> 00:37:15.220
And he noticed when he looked up

00:37:15.220 --> 00:37:16.620
that it was a very hot day

00:37:16.620 --> 00:37:18.380
but the cloud was covering him.

00:37:18.380 --> 00:37:19.940
Subhanallah.

00:37:19.940 --> 00:37:21.580
Imagine a hot day,

00:37:21.580 --> 00:37:22.700
enemies from all over,

00:37:22.700 --> 00:37:24.420
but the clouds are not your enemies.

00:37:24.420 --> 00:37:26.460
The creatures of Allah besides man,

00:37:26.460 --> 00:37:28.060
not your enemies.

00:37:28.060 --> 00:37:30.420
And this particular group of people,

00:37:30.420 --> 00:37:31.260
they were cursed.

00:37:31.260 --> 00:37:32.540
Imagine those hands

00:37:32.540 --> 00:37:35.540
that were pelting Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:37:35.540 --> 00:37:38.820
personally far worse than those hands

00:37:38.820 --> 00:37:40.620
that draw cartoons today

00:37:40.620 --> 00:37:43.620
although both of them are equal in blasphemy.

00:37:43.620 --> 00:37:47.620
May Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala safeguard us.

00:37:47.620 --> 00:37:52.010
So Utbah and Shaybah Ibn Rabi'ah,

00:37:52.010 --> 00:37:53.530
the two sons of Rabi'ah,

00:37:53.530 --> 00:37:55.130
they saw Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:37:55.130 --> 00:37:56.370
and these people are from Quraysh.

00:37:56.370 --> 00:37:58.770
They had their garden in Ta'if

00:37:58.770 --> 00:37:59.770
and they looked

00:37:59.770 --> 00:38:02.610
and they saw this man in blood, bleeding

00:38:02.610 --> 00:38:06.090
and they saw that he is helpless.

00:38:06.090 --> 00:38:08.490
No water, no drink, no food.

00:38:08.490 --> 00:38:11.250
So it is reported according to this narration

00:38:11.250 --> 00:38:12.650
that I have just made mention of,

00:38:12.650 --> 00:38:13.690
which is Mursal,

00:38:13.690 --> 00:38:15.810
it is reported that they sent Addas,

00:38:15.810 --> 00:38:17.690
the slave of theirs,

00:38:17.690 --> 00:38:20.410
they sent him with some grapes.

00:38:20.410 --> 00:38:21.370
Go and give that man.

00:38:21.370 --> 00:38:23.290
Just give it to him and come back.

00:38:23.290 --> 00:38:25.570
So when Addas went there,

00:38:25.570 --> 00:38:27.090
he gave the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:38:27.090 --> 00:38:28.970
the grapes and Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:38:28.970 --> 00:38:30.210
said Bismillah.

00:38:30.210 --> 00:38:31.730
As he said Bismillah,

00:38:31.730 --> 00:38:32.890
Addas looks at him and says,

00:38:32.890 --> 00:38:33.890
what did you say?

00:38:33.890 --> 00:38:35.130
Whatever you've said now,

00:38:35.130 --> 00:38:37.770
the people here don't even say that.

00:38:37.770 --> 00:38:40.330
So Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam said,

00:38:40.330 --> 00:38:42.450
obviously I said in the name of Allah

00:38:42.450 --> 00:38:44.530
and I'm eating in the name of Allah.

00:38:44.530 --> 00:38:45.690
Where are you from and who are you?

00:38:45.690 --> 00:38:47.050
He says, I am Addas

00:38:47.050 --> 00:38:49.690
and I come from Nineveh,

00:38:49.690 --> 00:38:51.810
which is in Iraq.

00:38:51.810 --> 00:38:54.690
And there, so before he could utter more,

00:38:54.690 --> 00:38:56.370
the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam says,

00:38:56.370 --> 00:39:00.770
that is the place where Yunus Ibn Mattah,

00:39:00.770 --> 00:39:04.530
Yunus, the son of Matthew is from,

00:39:04.530 --> 00:39:06.730
Yunus Alaihi Wasallam.

00:39:06.730 --> 00:39:07.850
So Addas was shocked.

00:39:07.850 --> 00:39:09.090
How do you know?

00:39:09.130 --> 00:39:10.530
How do you know?

00:39:10.530 --> 00:39:11.850
So the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:13.850
read some verses of the Quran

00:39:13.850 --> 00:39:16.050
where the story of Yunus is made mentioned.

00:39:16.050 --> 00:39:17.610
This Addas, it is reported,

00:39:17.610 --> 00:39:20.370
started kissing the forehead of Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:39:20.370 --> 00:39:22.090
and he declared, you're a messenger,

00:39:22.090 --> 00:39:23.010
you're a messenger.

00:39:23.010 --> 00:39:26.250
This is the one person who accepted Islam

00:39:26.250 --> 00:39:27.850
as he was leaving Ta'if.

00:39:27.850 --> 00:39:29.450
And now Utba and Shaiba,

00:39:29.450 --> 00:39:32.090
the sons of Rabi'ah are watching this Addas.

00:39:33.530 --> 00:39:35.370
And when he came back,

00:39:35.370 --> 00:39:36.250
what's your problem?

00:39:36.250 --> 00:39:38.010
How can you kiss that man?

00:39:38.050 --> 00:39:41.170
And he is a man whom you don't even know.

00:39:41.170 --> 00:39:42.130
What did he tell you?

00:39:42.130 --> 00:39:43.530
So he said, look,

00:39:43.530 --> 00:39:46.810
he told me something that only a prophet can know.

00:39:46.810 --> 00:39:48.050
That's it.

00:39:48.050 --> 00:39:49.490
They said, be careful of this man.

00:39:49.490 --> 00:39:51.050
And the narration ends there.

00:39:51.050 --> 00:39:53.050
May Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala save Goddess.

00:39:53.050 --> 00:39:56.690
It is a manna that I narrate to you or relate to you

00:39:56.690 --> 00:39:58.330
that that narration is mursal,

00:39:58.330 --> 00:40:01.770
which means the chain of narrators

00:40:01.770 --> 00:40:03.090
is not exactly complete,

00:40:03.090 --> 00:40:05.010
but most of the books of history

00:40:05.010 --> 00:40:07.250
have made mention of the story of Addas.

00:40:07.250 --> 00:40:09.410
So it's important for us to make mention of it.

00:40:09.410 --> 00:40:11.690
May Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala make us

00:40:11.690 --> 00:40:14.610
from amongst those who realize

00:40:14.610 --> 00:40:16.570
the true value of being Muslim.

00:40:16.570 --> 00:40:19.650
Wallahi, a great sacrifice has gone

00:40:19.650 --> 00:40:22.690
in getting this message across to us and to the globe.

00:40:22.690 --> 00:40:26.010
But this was all by the will of Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:40:26.010 --> 00:40:28.130
So the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:40:28.130 --> 00:40:29.530
then left Ta'if.

00:40:29.530 --> 00:40:31.930
And as he came back on his feet,

00:40:31.930 --> 00:40:32.890
he was walking,

00:40:32.890 --> 00:40:35.010
he stopped at a place called Wadi Nakhla

00:40:35.010 --> 00:40:36.410
for a few days.

00:40:36.450 --> 00:40:40.290
And he used to read Quran in the night in Salah.

00:40:40.290 --> 00:40:43.970
And Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala told him later on

00:40:43.970 --> 00:40:46.890
that when you were in that valley of Nakhla,

00:40:46.890 --> 00:40:47.970
a group of jinn,

00:40:47.970 --> 00:40:50.770
approximately seven of the jinn had come

00:40:50.770 --> 00:40:53.090
and they heard you recite the Quran.

00:40:53.090 --> 00:40:56.090
And Allah sent revelation to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:40:56.090 --> 00:40:58.850
telling him the following.

00:40:58.850 --> 00:41:04.170
And when We sent forth to you a group of jinn

00:41:04.170 --> 00:41:07.810
who were listening to the Quran,

00:41:07.810 --> 00:41:09.890
when they came to it,

00:41:09.890 --> 00:41:10.610
they said,

00:41:10.610 --> 00:41:13.010
I will give you advice.

00:41:13.010 --> 00:41:14.850
And when it was finished,

00:41:14.850 --> 00:41:17.290
they turned to their people,

00:41:17.290 --> 00:41:20.210
warning them.

00:41:20.210 --> 00:41:20.930
They said,

00:41:20.930 --> 00:41:22.650
O our people!

00:41:22.650 --> 00:41:25.610
We have heard a Book

00:41:25.610 --> 00:41:28.650
which was sent down after Moses.

00:41:28.650 --> 00:41:32.810
It confirms what is in front of it.

00:41:32.810 --> 00:41:35.810
It guides to the truth

00:41:35.810 --> 00:41:40.730
and to a straight path.

00:41:40.730 --> 00:41:42.370
O our people!

00:41:42.370 --> 00:41:46.410
Answer Allah's call and believe in it.

00:41:46.410 --> 00:41:47.770
Allahu Akbar!

00:41:47.770 --> 00:41:48.690
I will stop there.

00:41:48.690 --> 00:41:50.090
Powerful verses.

00:41:50.090 --> 00:41:51.290
Allah says,

00:41:51.290 --> 00:41:54.770
We had made the jinn come to you

00:41:54.770 --> 00:41:56.370
and listen to the Quran.

00:41:56.370 --> 00:41:57.650
When they heard it,

00:41:57.650 --> 00:42:01.370
they attended and they said to each other,

00:42:01.370 --> 00:42:05.330
stop in silence and listen to what is being recited.

00:42:05.330 --> 00:42:06.930
When they heard it,

00:42:06.930 --> 00:42:11.130
they immediately felt and they knew that this is the guidance.

00:42:11.130 --> 00:42:12.530
They believed in it,

00:42:12.530 --> 00:42:14.250
rushed back to their people,

00:42:14.250 --> 00:42:16.130
meaning to jinn kind and told them,

00:42:16.130 --> 00:42:17.770
O our jinn kind!

00:42:17.770 --> 00:42:22.170
We have just heard revelation after Moses,

00:42:22.170 --> 00:42:24.770
which is similar to that which he has brought

00:42:24.770 --> 00:42:25.690
and it is true

00:42:25.690 --> 00:42:27.850
and there is a messenger reciting it,

00:42:27.850 --> 00:42:30.450
believe in what he has brought

00:42:30.450 --> 00:42:34.820
and indeed you will be forgiven.

00:42:34.820 --> 00:42:36.540
The jinn kind are saying this.

00:42:36.540 --> 00:42:37.620
So Allah says,

00:42:37.620 --> 00:42:39.460
hang on, the jinn have believed.

00:42:39.460 --> 00:42:41.020
If the people of Ta'if

00:42:41.020 --> 00:42:45.060
told Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam to leave

00:42:45.060 --> 00:42:46.740
and they harmed him,

00:42:46.740 --> 00:42:47.980
these were jinn

00:42:47.980 --> 00:42:49.940
and they had accepted the message.

00:42:49.940 --> 00:42:52.300
But there is one thing that we need to know

00:42:52.300 --> 00:42:55.260
before this incident of the jinn.

00:42:55.300 --> 00:42:57.620
And that is as Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:42:57.620 --> 00:42:59.020
is leaving Ta'if,

00:42:59.020 --> 00:43:01.020
I made mention of Jibreel coming to him

00:43:01.020 --> 00:43:01.900
and telling him,

00:43:01.900 --> 00:43:03.620
you tell us what do you want?

00:43:03.620 --> 00:43:06.860
The angels of the mountains,

00:43:06.860 --> 00:43:08.580
they came to him and told him,

00:43:08.580 --> 00:43:10.740
O Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:43:10.740 --> 00:43:13.060
these people between these two mountains,

00:43:13.060 --> 00:43:15.420
you tell us we will crush them now.

00:43:15.420 --> 00:43:16.860
You just tell us,

00:43:16.860 --> 00:43:18.340
give us the instruction

00:43:18.340 --> 00:43:19.820
and we will deal with them.

00:43:19.820 --> 00:43:21.980
So Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:43:21.980 --> 00:43:23.380
he raises his hands,

00:43:23.380 --> 00:43:24.220
he says,

00:43:24.220 --> 00:43:26.780
اللهم إني أشكوا إليك ضعف قوتي

00:43:26.780 --> 00:43:28.140
وقلة حيلتي

00:43:28.140 --> 00:43:29.500
وهواني على الناس

00:43:29.500 --> 00:43:31.780
O Allah,

00:43:31.780 --> 00:43:33.220
I am complaining to you

00:43:33.220 --> 00:43:33.780
about what?

00:43:33.780 --> 00:43:34.780
About people?

00:43:34.780 --> 00:43:36.420
About these people of Ta'if?

00:43:36.420 --> 00:43:37.260
We can destroy them.

00:43:37.260 --> 00:43:37.860
No,

00:43:37.860 --> 00:43:40.820
I am complaining to you about my weakness.

00:43:40.820 --> 00:43:41.620
Ya Allah, I am weak.

00:43:41.620 --> 00:43:43.140
You sent me to Ta'if.

00:43:43.140 --> 00:43:43.860
I went to Ta'if,

00:43:43.860 --> 00:43:45.100
they didn't even listen.

00:43:45.100 --> 00:43:46.620
In Quraysh, they're not even listening.

00:43:46.620 --> 00:43:47.820
A handful of people,

00:43:47.820 --> 00:43:48.860
Ya Allah, this is happening.

00:43:48.860 --> 00:43:51.620
Ya Allah, I am complaining to you about my weakness

00:43:51.620 --> 00:43:52.620
and how weak I am.

00:43:52.620 --> 00:43:54.180
Subhanallah.

00:43:54.180 --> 00:43:57.260
And when this powerful messenger

00:43:57.260 --> 00:44:00.020
makes such a merciful remark

00:44:00.020 --> 00:44:01.620
looking at his weakness

00:44:01.620 --> 00:44:03.820
rather than the weakness of the others,

00:44:03.820 --> 00:44:04.820
not even weakness,

00:44:04.820 --> 00:44:06.660
the sin of the others,

00:44:06.660 --> 00:44:10.020
war crimes literally of the others.

00:44:10.020 --> 00:44:11.660
But Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam says,

00:44:11.660 --> 00:44:12.660
no, it's me who's weak.

00:44:12.660 --> 00:44:13.420
No, no, no.

00:44:13.420 --> 00:44:14.140
Then he says,

00:44:14.140 --> 00:44:15.980
اللهم مهدي قومي

00:44:15.980 --> 00:44:17.500
فإنهم لا يعلمون

00:44:17.500 --> 00:44:19.420
What I want from you now,

00:44:19.420 --> 00:44:21.860
Ya Allah, guide these people,

00:44:21.860 --> 00:44:23.220
guide my people

00:44:23.220 --> 00:44:26.020
because they don't know what they're doing.

00:44:26.020 --> 00:44:29.500
So the angel says to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:44:29.500 --> 00:44:32.100
we can destroy them at that juncture.

00:44:32.100 --> 00:44:33.260
Do you know what he says?

00:44:33.260 --> 00:44:34.740
He says, leave them.

00:44:34.740 --> 00:44:37.860
Perhaps Allah will take out from their progeny

00:44:37.860 --> 00:44:39.980
people who will accept my message.

00:44:39.980 --> 00:44:43.700
Imagine, look at how he is thinking of the future,

00:44:43.700 --> 00:44:44.980
praying for the future,

00:44:44.980 --> 00:44:46.980
having hope for the future.

00:44:46.980 --> 00:44:48.020
And he is saying,

00:44:48.020 --> 00:44:49.700
perhaps from their progeny,

00:44:49.700 --> 00:44:52.060
there will be people who will accept my message.

00:44:52.060 --> 00:44:55.620
Later on, you see how Saqeef accepted Islam.

00:44:57.260 --> 00:44:57.980
Subhanallah.

00:44:57.980 --> 00:44:59.700
Today you go to Ta'if.

00:44:59.700 --> 00:45:01.060
Who is there?

00:45:01.060 --> 00:45:02.380
Not a single non-Muslim.

00:45:02.380 --> 00:45:03.980
All the people of Ta'if are Muslim.

00:45:03.980 --> 00:45:07.100
Imagine, if Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:45:07.100 --> 00:45:09.580
Muhammad Ibn Abdullah had to say,

00:45:09.580 --> 00:45:10.460
destroy them,

00:45:10.460 --> 00:45:12.220
today there would be ruins in Ta'if.

00:45:12.220 --> 00:45:13.460
We would see the ruins.

00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:14.900
People will probably go there

00:45:14.900 --> 00:45:16.740
and make a tourist site out of it.

00:45:16.740 --> 00:45:18.340
And this is the weakness with us.

00:45:18.340 --> 00:45:20.620
We see the ruins of the previous nations.

00:45:20.620 --> 00:45:23.100
We convert them into a tourist resort,

00:45:23.100 --> 00:45:25.020
not thinking that we are actually supposed

00:45:25.020 --> 00:45:26.340
to be learning a lesson

00:45:26.340 --> 00:45:28.020
from whatever has happened.

00:45:28.020 --> 00:45:29.860
You can go, but on condition

00:45:29.860 --> 00:45:30.980
that you're learning a lesson

00:45:30.980 --> 00:45:33.860
and it's drawing you closer to Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:45:33.860 --> 00:45:36.540
May Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala safe guard us.

00:45:36.540 --> 00:45:38.300
So when Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:45:38.300 --> 00:45:39.020
now returned,

00:45:39.020 --> 00:45:40.980
we made mention of what happened with the jinn.

00:45:40.980 --> 00:45:42.460
And as he's going into Makkah,

00:45:42.460 --> 00:45:43.740
they didn't want him in Makkah.

00:45:43.740 --> 00:45:45.140
He couldn't enter.

00:45:45.140 --> 00:45:46.860
Because now he was out.

00:45:46.860 --> 00:45:48.180
They didn't want him back in.

00:45:48.180 --> 00:45:50.900
They wanted to fight him and kill him

00:45:50.900 --> 00:45:52.940
because he went to seek assistance

00:45:52.940 --> 00:45:56.180
from others against Quraysh.

00:45:56.180 --> 00:45:57.500
So at that juncture,

00:45:57.500 --> 00:45:59.620
he goes to Al-Mutrim Ibn Adi.

00:45:59.620 --> 00:46:00.500
And he says,

00:46:00.500 --> 00:46:02.980
look, I need you to guarantee for me

00:46:02.980 --> 00:46:05.060
or I need you to stand as guarantee for me

00:46:05.060 --> 00:46:06.860
so that I can enter into Quraysh.

00:46:06.860 --> 00:46:08.060
And as we said yesterday,

00:46:08.060 --> 00:46:10.060
this was the norm at the time.

00:46:10.060 --> 00:46:12.620
They used to give guarantees for one another

00:46:12.620 --> 00:46:13.500
on certain grounds.

00:46:13.500 --> 00:46:15.380
This man, I guarantee and so on.

00:46:15.380 --> 00:46:16.580
And please let him in.

00:46:16.580 --> 00:46:17.900
So Al-Mutrim Ibn Adi,

00:46:17.900 --> 00:46:20.260
his children got up with him.

00:46:20.260 --> 00:46:21.980
And it's reported some of his family members

00:46:21.980 --> 00:46:22.620
got up with him.

00:46:22.620 --> 00:46:23.420
They took their swords

00:46:23.420 --> 00:46:25.140
and they took Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:46:25.140 --> 00:46:26.060
right to the Ka'bah

00:46:26.060 --> 00:46:28.380
and allowed them to make tawaf around it.

00:46:28.380 --> 00:46:30.300
And the people of Quraysh are looking and saying,

00:46:30.300 --> 00:46:31.500
are you just following

00:46:31.500 --> 00:46:34.100
or is he under your guarantee?

00:46:34.100 --> 00:46:35.540
He says, he's under my guarantee.

00:46:35.540 --> 00:46:36.540
Subhanallah.

00:46:36.540 --> 00:46:37.340
Then they were quiet.

00:46:37.340 --> 00:46:38.220
They said, if that's the case,

00:46:38.220 --> 00:46:39.380
we leave him alone.

00:46:39.380 --> 00:46:41.260
And Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:46:41.260 --> 00:46:43.780
really had suffered at the hands of Quraysh

00:46:43.780 --> 00:46:45.700
directly and indirectly.

00:46:45.700 --> 00:46:47.580
There was another incident that occurred also,

00:46:47.620 --> 00:46:48.740
which was of great blessing.

00:46:48.740 --> 00:46:50.860
One man, one man from Dawos.

00:46:50.860 --> 00:46:54.420
Dawos was a tribe that was not so far.

00:46:54.420 --> 00:46:55.780
The people of Dawos,

00:46:55.780 --> 00:46:58.740
just one man had come,

00:46:58.740 --> 00:47:01.220
At-Tufail Ibn Amr,

00:47:01.220 --> 00:47:04.540
At-Tufail Ibn Amr al-Dawsi had come

00:47:04.540 --> 00:47:07.780
to see Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam in Makkah.

00:47:07.780 --> 00:47:09.140
And he saw him

00:47:09.140 --> 00:47:10.620
and immediately he accepted.

00:47:10.620 --> 00:47:11.860
He said, yes, this is the messenger.

00:47:11.860 --> 00:47:13.340
I believe and I bear witness.

00:47:13.340 --> 00:47:14.340
Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:47:14.340 --> 00:47:15.460
gave him some good news,

00:47:15.460 --> 00:47:16.820
read some Qur'an for him

00:47:16.820 --> 00:47:18.260
and told him, go back to your people,

00:47:18.260 --> 00:47:19.860
invite them to Islam.

00:47:19.860 --> 00:47:20.940
I'm making a dua,

00:47:20.940 --> 00:47:22.540
Allahumma hdi Dawsa,

00:47:22.540 --> 00:47:25.740
O Allah, guide the people of Dawos.

00:47:25.740 --> 00:47:27.700
When this At-Tufail Ibn Amr

00:47:27.700 --> 00:47:30.060
went back to Dawos,

00:47:30.060 --> 00:47:31.980
he conveyed the message

00:47:31.980 --> 00:47:34.780
and the majority of them turned to Islam.

00:47:34.780 --> 00:47:37.500
The majority of them turned to Islam.

00:47:37.500 --> 00:47:39.580
Do you know who is from Dawos

00:47:39.580 --> 00:47:41.380
for your information?

00:47:41.380 --> 00:47:44.260
A man who has narrated the most hadith

00:47:44.260 --> 00:47:46.340
of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:47:46.340 --> 00:47:49.460
His name is Abdulrahman ibn Sakhr,

00:47:49.460 --> 00:47:51.660
more commonly known as Abu Hurairah.

00:47:51.660 --> 00:47:53.620
Today we quoted him also in our talk,

00:47:53.620 --> 00:47:54.620
Abu Hurairah.

00:47:54.620 --> 00:47:58.500
His proper name is Abdulrahman ibn Sakhr.

00:47:58.500 --> 00:48:00.220
As we mentioned Abu Bakr,

00:48:00.220 --> 00:48:02.700
his proper name is Abdullah ibn Uthman.

00:48:02.700 --> 00:48:05.740
So here you have Abdulrahman ibn Sakhr.

00:48:05.740 --> 00:48:08.660
Abu Hurairah, he was a Dawsi

00:48:08.660 --> 00:48:10.700
and he had also accepted Islam

00:48:10.700 --> 00:48:13.700
and later on he met with Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:48:13.700 --> 00:48:15.180
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:48:15.220 --> 00:48:17.460
to open our doors and to grant us goodness.

00:48:17.460 --> 00:48:21.180
Now we have a very, very important incident

00:48:21.180 --> 00:48:23.580
that occurred at the time

00:48:23.580 --> 00:48:25.620
for Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:48:25.620 --> 00:48:27.220
and for the Muslims.

00:48:27.220 --> 00:48:29.460
Remember this 10th year of Hijrah

00:48:29.460 --> 00:48:31.580
was known as Amul Huzn.

00:48:31.580 --> 00:48:32.860
It was known, sorry,

00:48:32.860 --> 00:48:34.940
the 10th year of prophethood, not Hijrah.

00:48:34.940 --> 00:48:36.060
I think if I've said Hijrah,

00:48:36.060 --> 00:48:37.740
what I mean here is prophethood.

00:48:37.740 --> 00:48:39.100
Because as you know,

00:48:39.100 --> 00:48:41.380
there at that time they used to use

00:48:41.380 --> 00:48:44.060
some big incident that occurred

00:48:44.060 --> 00:48:45.540
and they used to count a year before it,

00:48:45.540 --> 00:48:47.060
a year after it, like we said,

00:48:47.060 --> 00:48:48.460
the year of the elephants.

00:48:48.460 --> 00:48:50.420
The next most important thing that happened

00:48:50.420 --> 00:48:52.860
was the year of prophethood

00:48:52.860 --> 00:48:54.260
and the next most important thing

00:48:54.260 --> 00:48:55.500
was the year of Hijrah

00:48:55.500 --> 00:48:56.460
and up to today,

00:48:56.460 --> 00:48:58.220
that was one of the most important things

00:48:58.220 --> 00:48:59.060
that occurred.

00:48:59.060 --> 00:49:00.820
So we say Hijri calendar,

00:49:00.820 --> 00:49:02.220
the calendar of Hijrah

00:49:02.220 --> 00:49:05.100
and we are sitting today at 1,433 years

00:49:05.100 --> 00:49:06.180
from that Hijrah.

00:49:06.180 --> 00:49:08.700
So what had happened is

00:49:08.700 --> 00:49:09.980
it was a year of sadness,

00:49:09.980 --> 00:49:11.100
the 10th year of prophethood.

00:49:11.100 --> 00:49:12.540
He lost his uncle,

00:49:12.540 --> 00:49:13.980
he lost his wife.

00:49:13.980 --> 00:49:16.140
He went to Taif and he was beaten

00:49:16.140 --> 00:49:18.380
and he was literally booted out

00:49:18.380 --> 00:49:19.980
and he came back from Taif

00:49:19.980 --> 00:49:22.580
and now he was in Mecca.

00:49:22.580 --> 00:49:25.060
And as a gift, Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:49:25.060 --> 00:49:28.380
in the 11th year of prophethood,

00:49:28.380 --> 00:49:32.420
granted him what is known as Al-Isra wal-Mi'raj,

00:49:32.420 --> 00:49:35.820
the journey by night and the ascension.

00:49:35.820 --> 00:49:38.140
And this, when did it happen?

00:49:38.140 --> 00:49:39.580
What was the date?

00:49:39.580 --> 00:49:42.700
The truth is there is no authentic narration

00:49:42.740 --> 00:49:44.980
giving us the precise date.

00:49:44.980 --> 00:49:45.820
So if someone says,

00:49:45.820 --> 00:49:47.500
oh, it is this date or that date,

00:49:47.500 --> 00:49:52.500
the reality is there is not an authentic narration.

00:49:52.500 --> 00:49:54.340
The bulk of the Muhaddithin say

00:49:54.340 --> 00:49:55.940
it happened in the month of Ramadan.

00:49:55.940 --> 00:49:57.100
Some of them say it happened

00:49:57.100 --> 00:49:58.780
towards the end of Rajab.

00:49:58.780 --> 00:50:00.060
Whatever be the case,

00:50:00.060 --> 00:50:01.780
we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:50:01.780 --> 00:50:04.980
to grant us a lesson from that Mi'raj.

00:50:04.980 --> 00:50:06.780
There's no point in debating this and that.

00:50:06.780 --> 00:50:09.420
We need to look at what is not debated.

00:50:09.420 --> 00:50:11.580
The issue of Isra and Mi'raj is not debated.

00:50:11.580 --> 00:50:14.300
So why debate about a little issue of the date?

00:50:14.300 --> 00:50:16.780
Let the date be something which is irrelevant for now.

00:50:16.780 --> 00:50:20.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us the lesson.

00:50:20.180 --> 00:50:25.180
So one day, the Prophet salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:50:25.220 --> 00:50:28.660
he used to sleep at the house of his cousin Ummuhani

00:50:28.660 --> 00:50:32.780
and as he was sleeping there,

00:50:32.780 --> 00:50:34.380
Jibreel alayhi salatu wa salam

00:50:34.380 --> 00:50:36.460
comes to him with a buraq.

00:50:36.460 --> 00:50:38.380
And one narration says he was in the Hijr.

00:50:38.380 --> 00:50:40.340
The Hijr meaning the Hatim.

00:50:40.380 --> 00:50:43.500
You know the Hatim area in the vicinity of the Kaaba.

00:50:43.500 --> 00:50:45.060
In fact, it is part of the Kaaba.

00:50:45.060 --> 00:50:47.300
We made mention of it, the semi-circular.

00:50:47.300 --> 00:50:49.420
Now, both narrations are correct

00:50:49.420 --> 00:50:52.140
because he was there and then he was brought here.

00:50:52.140 --> 00:50:53.340
So this is what happened.

00:50:53.340 --> 00:50:55.660
So he was at the house of Ummuhani

00:50:55.660 --> 00:50:59.740
and he was brought to where the well of Zamzam was.

00:50:59.740 --> 00:51:02.340
And when he was brought there, subhanallah,

00:51:02.340 --> 00:51:05.980
something massive happened, something huge happened.

00:51:05.980 --> 00:51:09.580
The occasion of the journey by night

00:51:09.580 --> 00:51:13.220
from Mecca all the way to Jerusalem

00:51:13.220 --> 00:51:16.740
and from Jerusalem, he was taken in Mi'raj.

00:51:16.740 --> 00:51:20.340
The meaning of Mi'raj, Mi'raj means an elevator.

00:51:20.340 --> 00:51:22.100
An elevator, that's the meaning of Mi'raj.

00:51:22.100 --> 00:51:24.860
So the buraq's job was to take him

00:51:24.860 --> 00:51:27.540
from Mecca to Jerusalem.

00:51:27.540 --> 00:51:29.660
And from Jerusalem, Mi'raj,

00:51:29.660 --> 00:51:31.300
the elevator took him all the way up

00:51:31.300 --> 00:51:33.620
with Jibreel alayhi salatu wa salam.

00:51:33.620 --> 00:51:35.220
And how did he go up?

00:51:35.220 --> 00:51:38.820
He went up physically in body and soul

00:51:38.860 --> 00:51:41.620
according to Ahlul Sunnah wal Jama'ah, subhanallah.

00:51:41.620 --> 00:51:42.620
You know, people, inshallah,

00:51:42.620 --> 00:51:45.060
we will talk in detail about this tomorrow.

00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:46.380
But sometimes people say,

00:51:46.380 --> 00:51:49.500
how could he have gone up in such a short while?

00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:51.140
And how could he have gone up?

00:51:51.140 --> 00:51:53.860
Believe me, today, we have rockets

00:51:53.860 --> 00:51:57.140
that take you into orbit within one and a half minutes.

00:51:57.140 --> 00:51:58.820
One and a half minutes, you are in orbit.

00:51:58.820 --> 00:51:59.860
They tell you that.

00:51:59.860 --> 00:52:02.900
What is impossible for Allah, subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:52:02.900 --> 00:52:05.020
They say, how could he have gone all the way

00:52:05.020 --> 00:52:08.420
to Jerusalem from Mecca in such a short space of time?

00:52:08.420 --> 00:52:09.780
Well, you have the Concorde

00:52:09.780 --> 00:52:13.340
that goes faster than 330 meters per second.

00:52:13.340 --> 00:52:14.460
That's the speed of sound.

00:52:14.460 --> 00:52:16.900
It breaks the sound barrier and it takes you.

00:52:16.900 --> 00:52:17.980
In fact, there is a bullet

00:52:17.980 --> 00:52:19.660
that travels even faster than that.

00:52:19.660 --> 00:52:21.780
May Allah, subhanahu wa ta'ala, grant us lesson.

00:52:21.780 --> 00:52:22.620
Tomorrow, inshallah,

00:52:22.620 --> 00:52:24.980
we'll commence with this story of Isra' and Mi'raj

00:52:24.980 --> 00:52:26.060
until we meet again.

00:52:26.060 --> 00:52:28.420
Wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala Nabina Muhammad.

00:52:28.420 --> 00:52:29.580
Subhanallah bi hamdi.

00:52:29.580 --> 00:52:30.860
Subhanaka allahum wa bi hamdika.

00:52:30.860 --> 00:52:32.460
Nashahdu alla ilaha illa anta.

00:52:32.460 --> 00:52:35.260
Nastaghfiruka wa natubu ilayk.

00:52:35.260 --> 00:52:40.420
Alif Laam Meem.

00:52:40.420 --> 00:52:44.620
Allah, la ilaha illa huwa l-Hijj al-Tayyum.
